{
  "texts": [
    "Distributed Ledger Technology (DLT) represents a paradigm shift in data management and information exchange, fundamentally transforming the way transactions are recorded, stored, and verified.",
    "At its core, the DLT is characterized by distributed and decentralized systems.",
    "It operates as a synchronized database across a network of nodes, each of which holds an identical ledger copy.",
    "By utilizing cryptographic techniques and consensus mechanisms, DLT ensures data integrity, security, and transparency.",
    "Transactions, once added, become immutable and tamper-evident, fostering trust among the participants (Rauchs et al., 2018)."
  ]
}